trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse"></xref> class is the base class for request response classes, like the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResponse"></xref> and <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.AddResponse"></xref> classes.

The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse.Controls"></xref> property contains an array of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryControl"></xref> objects returned by the server.
An array of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryControl"></xref> objects returned by the server.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse.ErrorMessage"></xref> property contains the error message, if any, for this operation.
The error message, if any, for this operation.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse.MatchedDN"></xref> property contains the matched distinguished name returned by the server.
The matched distinguished name returned by the server.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse.Referral"></xref> property contains the server referrals.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse.RequestId"></xref> property contains the Request Identifier.
User attempted to set the property value.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse.ResultCode"></xref> property contains the result code of the operation.
The result code of the operation.
